### Repository Conventions That Affect All Tasks

All modified files must pass the linter. The linter command is:

```bash
uv run prek run --files <modified-file>
```

Key linting rules enforced in this repository:

- MD031: All fenced code blocks must be surrounded by blank lines (before the opening fence and after the closing fence)
- All code fences must have a language specifier (`markdown`, `text`, `json`, `bash`, `yaml`, `python`)
- MD links must use `./` relative paths (never absolute paths, never bare backtick paths)
- Nested code blocks: outer fence uses 4+ backticks, inner uses 3 backticks (applies when showing markdown inside markdown)

The `.pre-commit-config.yaml` is run via `prek`, not `pre-commit`. Use `uv run prek run --files <file>` — not `pre-commit run`.

