### Pre-Existing Schema Divergences (Not in Scope)

The codebase analysis at `plan/codebase/plan-artifact-lifecycle.md` documents five divergences between `TASK_FILE_FORMAT.md` and actual task files in the repository:

1. `accuracy-risk` field is used in task files but not in the schema (ignored by parser)
2. `reason` and `handoff` fields appear in YAML frontmatter of newer task files but are not in the schema
3. `@` prefix on agent names in older task files conflicts with the schema example format
4. `issue-classification`, `scenario-target`, `analysis-method` fields existed in the schema before this feature added them (now documented)
5. Feature-context files accurately describe pre-implementation state; after implementation they diverge (expected, this is the problem this feature addresses)

These are not in scope for this implementation. Do not modify the schema for `accuracy-risk`, `reason`, `handoff`, or `@`-prefixed agent names in this set of tasks.

### Artifacts the `context-refinement` Agent (T5) Will Read During Freshness Checks

After T5 is deployed, the expanded `context-refinement` agent will locate plan artifacts by reading paths from the task file header and architecture spec header. These headers are the YAML frontmatter fields `architecture-spec` and `feature-context` in task files (e.g., this task file's frontmatter contains `architecture-spec: plan/architect-plan-artifact-lifecycle.md` and `feature-context: plan/feature-context-plan-artifact-lifecycle.md`). The agent will also read the `Intent Source` field from the plan artifact headers — a new field that new artifacts will have but existing ones lack. When `Intent Source` is absent, the agent defaults all divergences to `design-refinement` (safe default, no human review triggered).

